 on gluino mass accessible\nby this run of the LHC because the $\\chi^2/\\text{dof}$ of this model is well\nbelow $2\\sigma$ even for a gluino mass as high as 2.7 TeV. On the bright side,\nthis means that this model is still viable and we might find low energy SUSY\nparticles in the near future.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 27 Mar 2017 21:02:34 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 29 Mar 2017 18:34:17 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 18 Apr 2017 15:01:41 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-06-28"}
