 dimension to improve\nwalking classification. These holistic indexes can easily be interpreted in the\nframework of optimal movement complexity. Our developments may have immediate\napplications in rehabilitation, diagnosis, and classification procedures.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 28 Mar 2017 10:06:23 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 15 Jun 2017 15:01:01 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-02-07"}
